value.value: The proportion, quantity, or volume in whole blood, serum, or plasma of antibodies to insulin.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in the urine of this simple protein.

Any measurable characteristic related to the function of or processes in the two-lobed endocrine gland found in all vertebrates, located in front of and on either side of the trachea in humans, that produces various hormones, such as triiodothyronine and calcitonin.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the fibers that arise from the cells within the cerebral cortex layer V, pass through the medullary pyramid, and descend into the gray matter of the spinal cord.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the functional cells of the nervous system that receive, conduct, and transmit impulses.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the morphology or physiology during formation and differentiation of the transient structures of the embryo that develop into regions of the head and neck in higher vertebrates; in fish and amphibians, they support the gills.
The measured amplitude or duration of response to stimulation of AMPA receptors.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the measured amplitude or duration of response to stimulation of glutamanergic receptors.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the measured amplitude or duration of response to stimulation of NMDA receptors.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in the urine of organic acids containing a ketone group and a carboxylic acid group.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the crystalline particles composed of calcium carbonate and a protein which adhere to the gelatinous membrane of the maculae of the utricle and saccule (otolithic membrane).

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the gelatinous membrane which is supported by the stereocilia of the hair cells of the maculae of the saccule and utriculus of the inner ear; adhering to its surface are numerous calciferous crystalline particles called otoliths (statoconia).
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the process by which minerals (inorganic elements or compounds that have importance in body functions) are introduced into osseous tissue.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the duration of activity (physical or mental) an individual can endure.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in the urine of this salt or ester of phosphoric acid.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in whole blood, serum, or plasma of this regulator of calcium and phosphorus concentration.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the process of labor and delivery in female animals.
Any measurable characteristic related to the function of or processes in the endocrine glands positioned in relation to the superior end of each kidney.
The size or duration of currents detected in postsynaptic cells when an excitatory impulse arrives at the synapse causing depolarization.
The membrane potential detected in postsynaptic cells when an inhibitory impulse arrives at the synapse causing hyperpolarization.
The potential detected in postsynaptic cells when an excitatory impulse arrives at the synapse causing depolarization.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the communication from a neuron to a target across a synapse in the peripheral nervous system.
The degree of function or response of peripheral synapses to stimulation; these amplitudes are larger than central synapse potentials.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the duration of the reduction of effectiveness of synaptic connections between neurons and target after repetitive stimulation.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the response of central synapses when activated twice in rapid succession.

definition.value: indicative of defects in short-term plasticity due to lack of increase of neurotransmitter release at the second stimulus

value.value: The size or duration of potentials that persist after tetanic stimulation of central synapses.

label.value: central nervous system synapse formation trait

value.value: Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the process of generating connections between an axon and effector tissue or neuron.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the channels that secrete bile from the liver to the gall bladder and intestines.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the morphology or physiology of the channels that secrete bile from the liver to the gall bladder and intestines during their formation and differentiation.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the articulation point of two or more rigid skeletal components (bones, cartilage, or parts of a single bone).
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to blood flow to the synovial joint.
The size or duration of currents detected in postsynaptic cells when an inhibitory impulse arrives at the synapse causing hyperpolarization.
The time required for an axon to extend from a neuron cell body and find the target.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the developmental patterning of neurons.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the morphology or physiology during formation and differentiation of the transient and migratory group of cells that emerge from the dorsal region of the neural tube and disperse to many peripheral locations, ultimately differentiating to form various tissues of the adult.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the directed and orderly movement from point to point of the transient and migratory group of cells that emerge from the dorsal region of the neural tube and migrate to many peripheral locations, ultimately differentiating to form various tissues of the adult.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the signaling mechanisms that allow precise navigation and connections of axonal growth cones to effector tissues.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the connective tissue consisting of fat-storing cells and arranged in lobular groups or along minor blood vessels.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the thermogenic form of adipose tissue that is composed of brown adipocytes.

label.value: blood vessel smooth muscle size trait

value.value: Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical magnitude of the nonstriated, involuntary muscle tissue of the structures that convey blood throughout the body.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the directed and orderly movement of a germ cell, a cell specialized to produce haploid gametes, from point to point.
The proportion or number of cells in the innermost nuclear layer of the retina, which projects axons through the optic nerve to the brain.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in the urine of this metallic bivalent element with atomic symbol Ca and atomic number 20.
The total proportion, quantity, or volume of substances dissolved in urine, total solute amount.
The distance from point to point along the longest axis of the tube that conducts the urine from the renal pelvis to the bladder.
Any measurable characteristic related to the function of or processes in any of the small, sacculated organs found within the dermis that normally secrete sebum.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the controlled release of lipids onto the hair and skin from the sebaceous glands.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical magnitude of the two folded, sac shaped glands that are diverticula of the ductus deferens.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the process of the turnover of bone matrix that involves a balance of resorption and formation by osteoclasts and osteoblasts, respectively.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the flattened band of efferent fibers arising from the subiculum and medial border of the hippocampus, which then thickens to form the fornix and fibers of the hippocampal commissure.
